Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Combine Sandies(R) and melted butter in a mixing bowl. Press into a 9 x 13 inch baking pan. Bake for five minutes, remove from oven and proceed with recipe. Whisk together the remaining ingredients except the powdered sugar in a mixing bowl. Pour over cookie crust and bake for 20-25 minutes or until lightly browned. Let cool and dust with powdered sugar. Cut into 2 inch squares.